    "Then, the specificity is defined by the ratio of the TN and TN with FP, and accuracy is estimated to determine that how the classifier could actually predict the seizure-affected signals based on the set of features.",
    "The measures are defined as follows:",
    "(37) Sensitivity = TP TP + FN (38) Specificity = TN TN + FP (39) Accuracy = TP + TN TP + TN + FP + FN (40) Precision = TP TP + FP 5 and Table 6.",
    "The evaluation shows that the proposed GBSO-TAENN technique outperforms the other techniques with increased performance values.",
